          <span class="sam-case-outcome__stat kpi-value">600+</span>
          <span class="sam-case-outcome__label">sites covered</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 3. CUSTOMER CONTEXT ─── -->
  <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace heading, body, and details per case -->
  <section class="sam-case-context">
    <div class="sam-case-context__inner">
      <div class="sam-case-context__content">
        <p class="overline">Customer</p>
        <h2>Yorkshire Water</h2>
        <p class="lead sam-case-context__lead">One of the UK's largest water utilities, serving 5 million customers across Yorkshire. Their network includes hundreds of pumping stations, many unmanned, with thousands of rotating assets operating 24/7.</p>
        <div class="sam-case-context__details">
          <div class="sam-case-context__detail">
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-label">Industry</span>
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-value">Water &amp; Wastewater</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sam-case-context__detail">
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-label">Fleet size</span>
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-value">1,300+ rotating assets</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sam-case-context__detail">
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-label">Deployment</span>
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-value">600+ sites across Yorkshire</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sam-case-context__detail">
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-label">Primary scenario</span>
            <span class="sam-case-context__detail-value">Fleet-scale coverage (S2)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 4. THE CHALLENGE ─── -->
  <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace heading, body per case -->
  <section class="sam-case-challenge">
    <div class="sam-case-challenge__inner">
      <p class="overline">The challenge</p>
      <h2>70,000 annual inspections. Most of them told them nothing.</h2>
      <p class="lead sam-case-challenge__lead">Yorkshire Water's condition monitoring programme relied on periodic vibration surveys and manual inspections. The economics didn't work: most assets were submersible pumps — physically inaccessible without pulling them from the ground. Vibration sensors couldn't be installed. Inspections were scheduled by calendar, not by condition.</p>
      <p class="sam-case-challenge__body">The result: 30% of their rotating assets had no condition monitoring at all. Failures at unmanned stations went undetected until alarms triggered or sewage overflowed. Each pollution event carried regulatory, financial, and reputational consequences — costs that dwarfed the repair bill.</p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 5. THE SOLUTION ─── -->
  <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace heading, body, and solution items per case -->
  <section class="sam-case-solution">
    <div class="sam-case-solution__inner">
      <p class="overline">The solution</p>
      <h2>SAM4 deployed at the MCC — no access to the pump required</h2>
      <p class="lead sam-case-solution__lead">Samotics installed SAM4 ESA monitoring across Yorkshire Water's pump network. Current and voltage sensors were clamped at the motor control cabinet — not on the asset. No site modifications. No confined space permits. No disruption to operations.</p>

      <div class="sam-case-solution__items">
        <div class="sam-case-solution__item">
          <h3 class="sam-case-solution__item-title">Fleet-scale rollout</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-solution__item-desc">1,300 assets across 600+ sites connected in phases. Each installation took minutes at the MCC — no pump extraction, no scaffolding, no production downtime.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-case-solution__item">
          <h3 class="sam-case-solution__item-title">Continuous monitoring</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-solution__item-desc">Every connected pump monitored 24/7. SAM4 detects bearing degradation, blockages, cavitation, and efficiency losses as they develop — weeks before failure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-case-solution__item">
          <h3 class="sam-case-solution__item-title">Integrated with operations</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-solution__item-desc">SAM4 alerts integrated into Yorkshire Water's existing CMMS. Maintenance teams receive actionable alerts with fault context — no interpretation required.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 6. RESULTS ─── -->
  <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace results items and values per case -->
  <section class="sam-case-results">
    <div class="sam-case-results__inner">
      <p class="overline">Results</p>
      <h2>Quantified outcomes</h2>

      <div class="sam-case-results__grid">
        <div class="sam-case-results__card">
          <span class="sam-case-results__card-value kpi-value">&pound;9.8M</span>
          <h3 class="sam-case-results__card-title">Total benefits</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-results__card-desc">Combined savings from avoided failures, eliminated inspections, extended asset life, and operational efficiency improvements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-case-results__card">
          <span class="sam-case-results__card-value kpi-value">70,000</span>
          <h3 class="sam-case-results__card-title">Inspections replaced</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-results__card-desc">Manual vibration surveys and physical inspections replaced by continuous remote monitoring. Maintenance hours redirected to value-adding work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-case-results__card">
          <span class="sam-case-results__card-value kpi-value">0</span>
          <h3 class="sam-case-results__card-title">Pollution events from monitored assets</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-results__card-desc">Every monitored pump failure detected before it became a pollution incident. Early detection prevented sewage overflows and regulatory consequences.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sam-case-results__card">
          <span class="sam-case-results__card-value kpi-value">100%</span>
          <h3 class="sam-case-results__card-title">Coverage of target fleet</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-results__card-desc">From 30% monitored to full coverage across the critical asset fleet. No asset class excluded — including previously unmonitorable submersible pumps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 7. CUSTOMER QUOTE ─── -->
  <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace quote, attribution per case. Remove section if no quote available. -->
  <section class="sam-case-quote">
    <div class="sam-case-quote__inner">
      <blockquote class="sam-case-quote__blockquote">
        <p class="sam-case-quote__text">&ldquo;We&rsquo;ve chosen Samotics as our sole supplier for ESA technology for the coming years because they have shown strong performance in the water industry and are the only company able to deliver this technology at scale.&rdquo;</p>
        <footer class="sam-case-quote__attribution">
          <!-- TEMPLATE: Name, role, company -->
          <span class="sam-case-quote__name">Matt Armitage</span>
          <span class="sam-case-quote__role">Dynamic Maintenance Transformation Lead</span>
          <span class="sam-case-quote__company">Yorkshire Water</span>
        </footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 8. PDF DOWNLOAD + CTA ─── -->
  <section class="sam-case-cta">
    <div class="sam-case-cta__inner">
      <h2>Want the full story?</h2>
      <p class="lead sam-case-cta__lead">Download the complete case study, or request a demo to see how SAM4 could work for your operation.</p>
      <div class="sam-case-cta__actions">
        <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace PDF href per case -->
        <a href="/downloads/yorkshire-water-case-study.pdf" class="sam-btn sam-btn--primary">Download PDF</a>
        <a href="/contact?intent=demo" class="sam-btn sam-btn--outline">Request a Demo</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ─── 9. RELATED CASE STUDIES ─── -->
  <!-- TEMPLATE: Replace with 2–3 case studies in same industry or similar outcomes -->
  <section class="sam-case-related">
    <div class="sam-case-related__inner">
      <p class="overline">Related case studies</p>
      <h2>More results from the field</h2>

      <div class="sam-case-related__grid">
        <a href="/proof/southern-water" class="sam-case-related__card">
          <span class="sam-case-related__card-industry">Water &amp; Wastewater</span>
          <h3 class="sam-case-related__card-title">Southern Water</h3>
          <p class="sam-case-related__card-outcome kpi-value">63 failures caught, &pound;748K annual savings</p>
          <span class="sam-case-related__card-link">Read case study &rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/proof/vitens" class="sam-case-related__card">
          <span class="sam-case-related__card-industry">Water &amp; Wastewater</span>
          <h3 class="sam-case-related__card-title">Vitens</h3>
