      <p class="sam-case-challenge__body">The result: 30% of their rotating assets had no condition monitoring at all. Failures at unmanned stations went undetected until alarms triggered or sewage overflowed. Each pollution event carried regulatory, financial, and reputational consequences — costs that dwarfed the repair bill.</p>
